20,Consider the following recursive function to compute the factorial of a number: ```python def factorial(n): if n == 0: return 1 else: return n * factorial(n-1) ``` What is the time complexity of the above function for computing `factorial(n)`? A: \( O(n) \) B: \( O(n^2) \) C: \( O(2^n) \) D: \( O(\log n) \) E: \( O(n \log n) \) F: \( O(n^3) \) G: \( O(1) \) H: \( O(n!) \) I: \( O(\sqrt{n}) \) J: \( O(n^4) \)
21,"Which of the following best describes the impact of neo-colonialism on the economic development of post-colonial African states, as argued by dependency theorists and critical historians? A: Neo-colonialism led to the diversification of local economies and reduced dependence on former colonial powers. B: Neo-colonialism facilitated the development of strong, independent industrial sectors in post-colonial African states. C: Neo-colonialism perpetuated economic dependency and structural inequalities, hindering genuine economic development. D: Neo-colonialism primarily benefited the rural agricultural sector by providing advanced technology and infrastructure. E: Neo-colonialism led to a significant reduction in foreign debt and improved credit ratings for post-colonial African states. F: Neo-colonialism encouraged the equitable distribution of wealth and reduced income inequality within post-colonial African states. G: Neo-colonialism resulted in the establishment of democratic institutions and the rule of law in post-colonial African states. H: Neo-colonialism promoted the development of a robust and self-sustaining service sector in post-colonial African states. I: Neo-colonialism had a negligible impact on the economic development of post-colonial African states. J: Neo-colonialism led to the complete decolonization of economic policies and the autonomy of post-colonial African states."
